Measure the variability of your scores relative to the final score. Is your score always exactly 0.1 below the final score or does it oscillate above and below it? Calculated by subtracting the final score from your score for the categorye then taking the standard deviation of those values. This is always positive, a 0 represents your score is always the same distance from the final score and is practically impossible. Lower values are better, the best referees have a value aroun 0.10 while values above 0.30 indicate work is needed on the consistency of your scoring for the category.